			<h3 ><a href="#p143931">Re: 85 Raiding Enchanter- Specialisation</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=143931#p143931"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3003">Ishana</a></strong> &raquo; Aug 15th, '09, 10:21 </p>

			

			<div class="content">The benefits of Specialization are so minor that you are probably better off leaving it alone rather than going through the hassle of changing it and leveling up a new one.  If I remember right, Spec only reduces your mana cost, possibly reduces your fizzle rate, and increases your chance to regain your concentration if you are stunned.  Many choose Alteration because we have so many buffs, some choose Conjuration to get that extra edge for mezzes, go with Evocation if all you do is nuke, Abjuration and Divination are very poor choices for Enchanters.</div>

			

		</div>

		
