			<h3 ><a href="#p143942">Re: 85 Raiding Enchanter- Specialisation</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=143942#p143942"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5854">Aeulaven</a></strong> &raquo; Aug 16th, '09, 22:58 </p>

			

			<div class="content"><blockquote><div><cite>Conandx (taken from Sony boards) wrote:</cite>  I'm going to have to respectfully disagree.  Your specialization should be Evocation.  Here is why.  On a raid, you will never ever go out of mana buffing people (alteration) since 90% of buffing is done prior to the engage.  On a raid, you will never ever go out of mana mezzing things (conjuration).  I can chain cast pbae mez and stun on raids like tyranot for 20 minutes if need be, popping 2nd spire as needed.  There is no event in EQ that would require you to mez so much that you would ever risk going OOM.  The only thing that can run you OOM is nuking (evocation).  On every raid event enchanters do some mezzing, some stunning, some buffing, but only chain cast nukes.  I personally chain cast Polychaotics Assault alternating with Multichromatic Assault and throw in Mind Oscillate and Smother in between.  I've gone as far as to get Tweyne's Stone of Evocation to help with nuking efficiency. Just think through the events. Dt 1 we debuff adds, mez the mindgnawers as needed, and nuke.  Dt 2 we pbae mez/stun the first 3 waves of adds then nuke away the last 2 mobs and curator.  Event 3 we debuff and nuke.  Event 4 we pbae mez/stun and nuke the scryers.  Event 5 wedebuff,  pbae mez/stun and nuke the sacrifice mobs.  Event 6 we debuff, pbae mez/stun, nuke some, and charm.  Event 7 we debuff and nuke our asses off.  See the common theme.  Its the nuking and evocation that ultimately drains most of our mana and thus is the specialization an end game high end enchanter should master. <br /><br />    Conandx of Pandemonium on ZEK</div></blockquote><br />I picked up Evoc as my secondary for basically the same reason. Debated changing it but just left primary the original Conjuration for those few times where people are messing up and it turns into battlerez time, which you are operating basically off spire and your azure crystal (sometimes mana draw and lon click are down).</div>

			<div id="sig143942" class="signature">Kiillem: Are you tashing and ... umm, is this slowed? <br />ranger23987: haste wmp<br />Aeulaven:  Tash that, Slow this, Buff me... wtf!?<br />Aeulaven: F***ing shamans have you guys spoiled.</div>

		</div>

		
