			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=143953#p143953"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5966">Conandx</a></strong> &raquo; Aug 17th, '09, 20:37 </p>

			

			<div class="content">Another reason to consider Evocation as your primary specialization is soloing.  Sometimes when I need to camp some items and charm isnt a good idea for whatever reason, it comes in handy as well.  An example was me camping Prismatic Gemstone in Crystallos a couple of days ago.  I would tash, slow the mob, cast 4 dots on it (Mind, Smother, Strangling air, Thin air) and alternate nuke with polychaotic/multichromatic assault.  This all while having twincast aura and mana reiterate aura running.  I ran oom over time by nuking this way nonstop.  End result is 3 hours of killing elementals and that shiny new aug u can see in my shield on magelo.  But hey, if you think you will run oom by buffing the raid or by mezzinng  mindgnawers, by all means go a different route.  Personally I think the choice is clear.</div>

