			<h3 ><a href="#p143983">Re: 85 Raiding Enchanter- Specialisation</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=143983#p143983"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5732">Jesliya</a></strong> &raquo; Aug 21st, '09, 00:15 </p>

			

			<div class="content">I was one of the big advocates for conjuration speccing recently, but i've thought about it since. In my mind there's no question it was the way to go not too long ago, and I'm glad I did. But mezes have changed a lot since then, and I don't think conjuration really applies any more. For one thing the mana cost on mez has stayed pretty low.<br /><br />But more importantly, since they gave us mez mastery 2, solo pbae mez has become a pretty safe and viable option. Conjuration was great back when pbae mez couldn't hold the line and just gave us a burst lock down ability. Then we had to do a lot of detailed mez management, and it meant a lot of casts. Nowadays if I have a huge chunk of mobs, I'll just pbae and I can do that all day long.<br /><br />I need to go re-spec sometime.</div>

			

		</div>

		
