			<h3 ><a href="#p144022">Re: 85 Raiding Enchanter- Specialisation</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=144022#p144022"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1501">Sunaeri</a></strong> &raquo; Aug 25th, '09, 16:10 </p>

			

			<div class="content">Based on what you presented, I doubt this will change your argument; however, the targeted AoE mezzes are also conjuration.<br /><br />You make a decent argument.  I am seriously considering changing my primary to divination.  <br /><br />The PBAoE mezzes are only safer on the remezz though, not the initial mez.  Really, the remez is always safer than the initial mez no matter which kind of mez you are casting.  The PBAoE stuns always have a gap, so there is danger on every recast.  Since we are mentioning stuns, the single target stun line also falls under alteration.  Although I hardly see that ranking in comparison to the other spell lines under consideration.  It is more likely that Charm is the only CC that will work on the mob in the raiding environment than it is in the groupping environment.  So raiding raises the value of Alteration.<br /><br />Doing the quest Respecialization resets both your primary specialization and your secondary forte, correct?<br /><br />Here are the spells in list form because I am still considering which I want for secondary now<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Divination</span>:  PBAoE Mez/PBAoE Stun<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Conjuration</span>: Targetted Mezzes (Single and AoE)<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Alteration</span>: Charm and Single Target Stun<br /><br />We need a tertiary specialization! (just kidding btw)</div>

			

